Then mix them with the onions, mango, tomato, spinach and avocado and toss the salad in the vinaigrette. Leave the salad to infuse for at least 15 mins.
Preheat the oven to 425°F. Brush the bread lightly with 2 tbsp of olive oil and spread the cheese over it. Put the bread on a baking sheet and bake it for about 10 mins. Serve with the salad.

title: steak sandwich
directions: Heat olive oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Cook steaks for 1-2 mins per side, or until cooked to your liking. Transfer to a plate.
Add red onion and tomatoes to pan. Saute for 4-5 mins, until tender, turning tomatoes once.
Spread barbecue sauce over 4 slices of toast. Top each with mixed greens, steak, tomato, onion and remaining toast. Serve.

title: striped frog jellies (for kids)
directions: Place 6 plastic tumblers on a tray. Place a frog and plastic spoon in each.
Prepare strawberry jello according to package instructions. Pour into prepared cups and chill until set.
Prepare lime jello according to package instructions. Let cool slightly then pour over set strawberry jello. Chill until set.

title: creamy salmon and mushroom fettuccine with garlic breadcrumbs
directions: To make the garlic breadcrumbs, process pita breads into coarse crumbs in a food processor or chop with a knife. Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Add breadcrumbs, thyme and 2 cloves garlic. Fry until golden and crunchy. Remove from pan and set aside to cool on paper towels.

To make the salmon and mushroom fettuccine, heat oil in a frying pan over medium-low heat. Cook remaining garlic for 3 mins, or until soft. Add mushrooms and cook for 10 mins, or until soft and most liquid has evaporated. Add wine. Bring to a boil and cook for 1 min. Add cream and Parmesan. Simmer until reduced by 1/2. Add salmon, lemon zest, herbs and spinach. Cook for 5 mins, or until heated through. Season.
Meanwhile, cook fettuccine in a boiling salted water until al dente. Drain then toss with sauce. Distribute between serving bowls and sprinkle with garlic breadcrumbs. Drizzle with lemon juice.

title: savory ground beef
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Saute onion and garlic for 2-3 mins until the onion is tender.
Add ground beef to the onion mixture and cook for 4-5 mins until well browned, breaking up with a spoon as it cooks.
Stir in mushrooms, carrot and celery, mixing well. Cook, stirring, for 5 mins.

Add tomatoes, water and tomato paste. Season to taste, then bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer for 10 mins or until vegetables are tender. Stir in parsley. Serve on toast, sprinkled with additional parsley. Accompany with mixed greens.

title: potato, spinach and tuna casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease an 8 cup baking dish.

In a medium saucepan, melt the butter on high. Stir in the flour and cook for 1 minute. Remove from heat and gradually mix in the milk until smooth. Return to the heat and cook, stirring, until the sauce boils and thickens. Reduce the heat and simmer for 3 mins. Stir in the tuna, parmesan and lemon zest and season to taste.

Arrange half the potato slices in the dish. Layer with half the spinach, half the onion and one-third tuna sauce. Repeat the layers, finishing with the tuna sauce. Cover with foil and bake for 30 mins.
Uncover and sprinkle with the extra parmesan. Bake for a further 15-20 mins until the potatoes are tender and the top is golden.

title: lunchbox pesto pasta salad
directions: Toss together pasta, sauce, and tomatoes until well combined. Transfer to an airtight container or lunch box. Chill until required. Serve with salad leaves.

title: spaghetti in mushroom, tomato & pumpkin sauce
directions: Cook the spaghetti in boiling salted water according to the package instructions. For the sauce, heat 2 tbsp of oil in a large frying pan. Add the mushrooms and saute them for about 3 mins. Remove them from the pan and season them to taste. Put the pumpkin in the pan and cook it for about 4 mins. Add the onion, garlic and tomato and cook for 3 more mins. Add the tomato puree and saute briefly. Drain the spaghetti, reserving about 2/3 cup of the cooking water.
Add the 2/3 cup water, spaghetti, mushrooms and thyme to the pumpkin and tomato sauce. Bring to a boil and stir briefly. Add the sugar and lemon peel and season to taste. Serve garnished with thyme.

title: beef, black eyed pea and spinach soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Cook onion and garlic, stirring, until onion softens. Add stock, wine, tomato paste and beef. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 40 mins. Uncover and simmer for 30 mins. Remove beef from pan. When cool enough to handle, remove and discard fat and sinew. Coarsely chop.

Meanwhile, add black eyed peas to soup and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until beans are tender. Return beef to pan along with spinach. Simmer, uncovered, until soup is hot. Season to taste.

title: seafood soup with gremolata
directions: In a large saucepan, combine fish bones, 1 onion, carrot, celery, peppercorns, bay leaves and 8 cups water. Simmer for 20 mins. Strain stock, discarding bones and vegetables.

Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Cook garlic and remaining onion, stirring, until onion has softened. Add tomatoes and sugar. Cook, stirring, for 10 mins, or until tomatoes are soft. Add canned tomatoes, tomato puree and wine. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for 5 mins, or until mixture thickens slightly, stirring occasionally. Add stock and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 mins. Let cool for 10 mins.
Blend or process tomato soup, in batches, until smooth. Return to pan and bring to a boil. Add lobster and fish. Simmer, stirring, for 5 mins, or until seafood is just cooked. Season to taste.
To make the gremolata, combine all ingredients in a small bowl. Serve soup sprinkled with gremolata.

title: salmon with watercress hollandaise
directions: For the watercress hollandaise, puree 3/4 of the watercress in a food processor with 2-3 tbsp of water. Melt the butter slowly in a small saucepan. Remove from the heat and let cool. Whisk the egg yolks and 1/2 cup of the wine in a bowl set over a saucepan of simmering water (do not let base of bowl touch water). Gradually whisk in the melted butter. Stir in the watercress puree and sugar and season to taste. Keep warm.

Cut the salmon fillet in half lengthwise and slice it thinly. Place remaining 1/2 cup wine, stock, lemon juice and 1 tsp of salt in a large skillet on medium-low heat. Bring to a simmer. Add salmon and simmer for 4-5 mins.
Serve the fish with the watercress hollandaise. Sprinkle with the remaining watercress.

title: walnut golden raisin loaf
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with a double thickness of parchment paper.
Place the golden syrup, sugar, milk and raisins in a small saucepan on medium heat. Stir gently until the sugar has dissolved. Cool. Mix in the lemon peel and egg.
Sift the flour, salt and baking powder into a large bowl. Stir in the walnuts. Gradually stir in the raisin mixture. Pour into the prepared pan.
Bake for about 1 hour, until golden brown and toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.
Serve sliced with butter. Keep any unsliced loaf wrapped in parchment paper in an airtight container.

title: tapioca and coconut pudding
directions: Bring a large saucepan of water to a boil and add the tapioca pearls, stirring so they don't stick the bottom of the pan. Cook for 20 mins, or until the tapioca pearls are almost transparent, stirring from time to time. Drain, then rinse with cold water.
Place the sugar and coconut cream in a small saucepan and heat until the sugar dissolves. Place in a bowl along with the tapioca and stir to combine.
Divide the mixture between 4 serving bowls and refrigerate for 30 mins, or until ready to serve. Top with sliced mango.

title: turkey steaks with asian slaw
directions: In a large, shallow bowl, combine soy sauce, sugar, mirin and garlic. Add turkey and turn to coat. Chill for 1 hour.
Heat a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook turkey for 3-4 mins per side, until cooked through.

To make the slaw, combine cabbage, noodles, carrot and spring onions in a large bowl. Whisk together peanut oil, sesame oil, soy sauce, sugar and lemon juice. Pour over slaw and toss to combine. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and serve with turkey.

title: chargrilled vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine arugula, croutons, vegetables and olives.
Place olive oil, basil, lemon juice and anchovy fillets in a food processor or blender. Process until smooth. Season. Drizzle over salad and toss well.
Top with feta and serve with prosciutto and crusty bread.

title: easy calzone
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, yeast, sugar and salt. Make a well in centre. Gradually add water, stirring to form a soft dough (you may need an extra 50ml water to do this).
Turn onto a floured surface; knead 10 minutes, until smooth and elastic. Place in a lightly oiled bowl; set aside, covered with a clean tea towel, until doubled in size (about 1 hour).
Preheat oven to moderate, 180°C./ 160°C. fan. Gas mark 4. Lightly grease 2 oven trays.
Punch down dough with fist; knead 2-3 minutes, then divide into 6 pieces. Roll out on lightly floured surface into 15cm rounds.
Top with filling of choice. Brush edges with water; fold dough over and press to seal. Set aside 15 minutes, to rise slightly.
Bake 20-25 minutes, until calzone are golden. Serve with salad, if liked.

title: fettuccine carbonara
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water for 8-10 mins, or until al dente. Drain.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Add garlic and cook, stirring, for 30 seconds, or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Add bacon and cook, stirring, for 4-5 mins, or until browned. Add spinach and stir until just wilted. Remove from heat and toss with pasta.
Whisk eggs, cream and 1/2 the Parmesan together then toss with pasta mixture. Transfer to shallow serving bowls and serve sprinkled with garlic, parsley and remaining Parmesan.

title: fruit salad in spiced syrup
directions: Place 1 cup water and sugar in a small saucepan on low heat. Stir until the sugar has completely dissolved.

Add the vanilla bean and seeds, cinnamon stick and cardamom pods. Bring to a boil without stirring. Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 5 mins without stirring. Remove from heat and cool. Remove vanilla pod, cinnamon stick and cardamom pods.
Pour cooled syrup over fruit in a large shallow dish. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hr, stirring occasionally, before serving.

title: piña coladas
directions: In a blender, combine ice, pineapple juice, coconut milk, liqueur and lime juice. Blend until combined. Distribute between 6 serving glasses. Decorate each with a pineapple wedge.

title: coffee and caramel peanut bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease a 15 x 12 inch baking sheet. Beat the butter and 2/3 cup of sugar with the whisk of a mixer until creamy. Beat in the eggs one at a time.

In a saucepan, heat 1/4 cup of milk and stir in the coffee until dissolved. Add the remaining milk and remove from the heat. Sift the flour and baking powder together and gradually stir into the egg mixture, alternating with the coffee milk, until everything is incorporated. Spoon into the baking sheet and smooth out. Bake for 15 mins. Remove from the oven and drizzle with the liqueur.
In a saucepan, heat 1 1/4 cups of sugar and 5 tbsp water until caramelized. Stir in the cream, and the peanuts. Simmer for 1 min. Spread over the cake and allow to cool.
In a separate saucepan, heat 1/3 cup of sugar and 1 tbsp water until golden brown and caramelized. Using a teaspoon, drizzle in a crisscross pattern on a sheet of parchment paper. Allow to set.
Cut the cake into 24 bars. Break the caramel lattice into pieces and use to decorate the bars.

title: fish fingers with coleslaw
directions: To make the coleslaw, combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Set aside to marinate.

Grease an 8x12 inch baking dish. To make the fish fingers, blend or process fish and chives until smooth. Press mixture evenly into dish and chill until set. Once set, turn out onto a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Cut into 8 slices then cut each slice in 1/2 to make 16 fish fingers.
In a shallow bowl, whisk egg whites lightly. Place breadcrumbs in a separate shallow bowl. Dip fish fingers into egg whites then in breadcrumbs to coat.
In a large frying pan, heat oil over medium-high heat. Cook fish fingers, in batches, for 3 mins, or until lightly browned and cooked through. Drain on paper towels. Season and serve with coleslaw.

title: glazed chicken drumsticks with chickpea salad
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Rub the chicken drumsticks with 2 tbsp of the oil. Sprinkle over the paprika and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Place on a baking tray and bake for 35-40 mins until cooked through and the skin is crispy.
Meanwhile, mix 2 tbsp of the honey with 2 tbsp water. Brush over the chicken legs 5 mins before the end of cooking time.
To make the salad dressing, mix the remaining honey with the orange juice, vinegar and remaining oil. Season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper.

Place the chickpeas in a bowl with the cherry tomatoes and avocado. Drizzle over the dressing and toss well. Toss through the chopped herbs just before serving. Serve with chicken and garnish with the extra chervil sprigs.

title: zesty chicken burgers
directions: Combine the ground chicken, egg, sage and lemon peel in a large bowl. Season and mix well. Shape evenly into 4 patties. Cover and refrigerate for 20 mins.
Heat 1 tbsp of the oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Saute the onion for 2-3 mins, stirring occasionally, until tender. Remove from the pan and keep warm. Wipe the pan clean.

Dust the patties in seasoned flour, shaking off the excess. Flatten slightly. Heat the remaining 2 tbsp oil in the same pan on medium heat. Cook the patties for 4-6 mins each side, until golden and cooked through. Squeeze the lemon juice over the patties.
Spread the mayonnaise on the bread and top 4 slices with salad leaves, onion and patties. Top with the remaining bread slices and serve.

title: pesto potato salad
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling water for about 20 mins. Mix the diced onion with the pesto and stock. Drain the potatoes, rinse them in cold water and cut them in half. Mix the salad, potatoes and pesto dressing and serve them in a large bowl, garnished with Prosciutto.

title: lamb and mint tagine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Toss lamb in flour, shaking off excess.

Heat olive oil in a heavy-bottomed Dutch oven over high heat. Working in batches, cook lamb for 3-5 mins, until browned. Return all of lamb to pan along with Moroccan seasoning, squash, chickpeas, chicken stock, lemon zest and lemon juice. Bring to a boil, cover and transfer to oven to braise for 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until lamb is very tender.
Sprinkle with mint and serve with toasted Turkish bread.

title: spicy prawn and cabbage tagliatelle
directions: Heat 1 tbsp oil in a saucepan, add the onion, cabbage and chili and saute for 2-3 mins. Add the orange juice and 1/2 cup water and bring to a boil. Mix in the crushed bouillon cube then cover and simmer for 10-15 mins, until the cabbage is tender.
Cook the pasta in salted boiling water according to the package instructions.

Meanwhile, heat the remaining oil in a frying pan, add the garlic and prawns and stir-fry for 3-4 mins until cooked through. Season. Drain the tagliatelle then toss with the cabbage and prawns. Serve.

title: cod with creamy spicy rice and mango salsa
directions: For the mango salsa, mix 2/3 of the lime juice with the powdered sugar and 6 tbsp of olive oil. Stir in the diced tomato, mango and onions then season to taste.
For the creamy spicy rice, cook the rice according to the package directions then drain. Stir in the creme fraiche and hot Italian seasoning mix.

Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 300°F. Put the cod fillets in an ovenproof dish and sprinkle them with pieces of butter. Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 8-10 mins. Turn off the heat and leave the fish in the oven for about 5 mins.
To finish, mix the remaining lime juice with a little salt and 4 tbsp of oil then toss with the curly endive. Serve the cod and rice with the mango salsa and salad on the side.

title: pineapple and mint slushie
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: green apple, blue cheese, cranberry and pistachio salad
directions: Distribute salad greens and apple wedges between 4 serving plates. Sprinkle with pistachios, blue cheese and cranberries.
To make the orange dressing, whisk together orange juice, olive oil, vinegar, mustard and garlic until combined. Drizzle over salad and toss to combine. Serve immediately.

title: ham and avocado spinach salad with mustard vinaigrette
directions: Boil, steam or microwave peas until tender; drain. Rinse under cold water and drain again.
To make mustard vinaigrette, combine garlic, vinegar, parsley, ginger, mustard, oil and 1 tbsp warm water in a screw-top jar; shake well.
Place peas in large bowl with remaining ingredients; toss gently to combine.
Divide salad among serving plates; drizzle with vinaigrette.

title: baked fish with fennel and tomato
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Lightly coat a nonstick frying pan with oil. Cook onions over low heat for 3 mins, until soft. Add tomatoes and cook for 1 min. Remove from heat and add bread, parsley and milk. Season.

Make 2 diagonal cuts through the thickest part of each side of fish. Fill cavity with some of the bread mixture. Arrange fennel in a baking pan and top with fish. Season then sprinkle remaining bread mixture over top. Drizzle with olive oil and cover with foil. Bake for 25 mins, until just tender.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: lamb chops with mint hollandaise
directions: Preheat outdoor grill to high. Brush lamb with melted butter or oil and season well. Cook for 2-3 minutes each side, until cooked to your liking.
Whisk mint and cayenne pepper into warm Hollandaise sauce.
Toss together hot potato halves and parsley.
Serve lamb with potatoes and drizzle with mint Hollandaise.

title: grilled chili chicken with tomato salsa
directions: Combine 1 tbsp oil, 1/2 the chili, 1/2 the cilantro, lemon zest, ginger and garlic. Rub onto chicken, cover with plastic wrap and chill for 10 mins to marinate.
Meanwhile, to make the salsa, combine tomato, onion and remaining oil, chili and cilantro. Season and set aside.
Preheat broiler or grill. Cook chicken, in batches, for 2 mins per side, or until brown and cooked through. Transfer to a plate, cover with foil and let rest for 5 mins. Slice and serve with salsa.

title: crostini with feta, artichokes and arugula
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F.

Spray both sides of bread slices with no stick cooking spray. Place on a baking pan. Toast until browned on both sides and crisp. Rub one side of each crostini with cut-side of garlic. Place crostini on platter.
Toss arugula with oil and vinegar in medium bowl; season to taste.
Top crostini with arugula mixture, artichokes and cheese. Sprinkle with freshly cracked black pepper.

title: lamb and halloumi kebabs
directions: In a shallow dish, combine lemon juice, garlic and oregano. Add lamb and toss to coat. Cover and marinate in the fridge for at least 2 hours, basting occasionally.

Preheat a grill or grill pan on medium. Thread lamb and halloumi onto skewers. Grill for 8-10 mins, turning and basting with marinade, until cooked and cheese is golden. Add lemon halves to grill and cook 3-4 minutes, until warmed through.
To make herbed salad, toss all ingredients together in a large bowl and season to taste.
Serve skewers with salad, grilled lemon and flatbread.

title: one-pot potatoes and pork
directions: Heat 2 tbsp oil in a large frying pan, add meat and brown. Season and add paprika then remove from pan. Add remaining oil and saute potatoes for about 10 mins, turning. Add mushrooms and spring onions and cook for another 5 mins. Add onion soup powder then cream and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil, return meat to pan and cook over low heat, covered, for about 10 mins. Serve garnished with reserved spring onion.

title: lamb rogan josh
directions: Set aside leaves from cilantro; cover and refrigerate.
Heat 1 tbsp of the oil in large skillet on high heat. Cook lamb, in batches, for about 2-4 mins, or until well browned. Remove from pan.

Reduce heat to medium. Add remaining oil. Cook onion and garlic, stirring, for about 4 mins, or until onion softens. Stir in cilantro stems and roots. Add curry paste; cook, stirring, for about 2 mins, or until fragrant. Add lamb, tomato puree and 1 cup water; stir to combine. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

Add sweet potato to pan. Cover; simmer for about 30 mins, or until lamb and vegetables are tender. Stir chickpeas into pan; simmer until heated through. Stir in spinach and cilantro leaves. Season to taste before serving.

title: stuffed quail eggs and king prawn canapés
directions: Place the eggs in a pan of cold water, bring to a boil and cook for 4 mins. Drain and rinse under cold water for 2-3 mins. Peel.
Place the mayonnaise, prawns and lemon juice in a bowl and puree with an immersion blender. Stir in the dill and paprika. Season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper.

Cut the eggs in half and remove the yolks, stir the yolks into the prawn mixture and mix well. Spoon into a piping bag fitted with a small round nozzle. Pipe into the egg centers and chill until ready to serve. Just before serving garnish with the radish slices and extra dill.

To make the marinated king prawns, place 2 tbsp of the oil in a bowl with the garlic, chili powder and coriander powder. Add the king prawns and stir well to coat in the marinade. Chill for 30 mins to allow the flavors to develop.
Meanwhile, place the tomato in a pan of boiling water, simmer until the skin splits. Remove from the water with a slotted spoon. When cool enough to handle peel off the skin. Finely chop.

Heat the remaining oil in a frying pan, fry the king prawns for 3 mins, add the chopped tomato and lime juice and cook for a further minute. Season to taste with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Serve on wooden cocktail sticks. Garnish with fresh coriander.

title: spare ribs with potato wedges and corn
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Line 2 baking trays with baking paper.
In a large bowl, combine honey, vinegar, tomato paste, mustard and chili. Reserve 1/4 cup. Add ribs to bowl, tossing to coat.
Arrange ribs in a single layer on 1 tray. Cover with foil. Bake for 50-55 mins.

Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine potatoes, corn, oil and paprika. Toss to coat and season to taste. Wrap each piece of corn in foil. Arrange corn and wedges in single layer on remaining tray. Bake for last 10 mins of ribs cooking time.
Increase temperature to 400°F. Remove all foil. Brush ribs with reserved marinade. Bake both trays for 10 more mins. Serve ribs as racks or sliced individually with potato wedges and corn.

title: apple and ricotta fritters
directions: Combine ricotta, flour, sugar, nutmeg, egg and apple in a medium bowl.
Heat oil in a large saucepan to 350°F. Working in batches, deep-fry rounded tablespoons of ricotta mixture until golden brown. Transfer to paper towels to drain. Toss fritters in cinnamon sugar.
Serve drizzled with maple syrup.

title: spiced lamb tart
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet on high heat. Saute onion for 6 mins. Add the lamb, red pepper and carrots and cook for 6 mins, until meat is browned.
Add coriander, cayenne pepper and 1/2 tsp of the cumin seeds and cook for 1 min. Add flour and cook, stirring, for 1 min.
Add stock and bring to a boil. Cook for 5 mins until sauce thickens. Remove from heat and set aside to cool.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Roll out 1 of the crusts on lightly floured surface to 11-inch round. Line bottom and sides on greased 9-inch springform pan with rolled-out crust. Spoon lamb mixture into crust. Place remaining crust over filling. Brush edges with water. Pinch together top and bottom crusts to seal. Sprinkle top with remaining 1/2 tsp cumin seeds.
Bake for 40-45 mins until filling is heated through and crust is browned.

title: lemon and herb chicken with vegetables
directions: Combine garlic, lemon zest, chopped parsley and thyme. Season. Add chicken and toss to coat. Set aside.
Boil potatoes until tender. Drain.
Meanwhile, cook tomatoes and asparagus on a heated oiled grill pan (or broil) until tender. Combine with potatoes, lemon juice, olive oil and parsley leaves. Season and cover to keep warm.
Cook chicken on grill pan (or in broiler) until browned on both sides and just cooked through. Serve with vegetables and tomato chutney.

title: pasta bolognese
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over high heat and saute onion for 2-3 mins, until tender. Add ground beef and brown. Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, wine and 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and add pasta. Simmer for 15-20 mins, stirring occasionally, until pasta is tender. Season. Serve with parsley and Parmesan.

title: chinese barbecued spare ribs
directions: Combine barbecue sauce, soy sauce, honey, orange juice, sugar, garlic and ginger in a large shallow dish. Add ribs and turn to coat. Cover and chill for 3 hours, or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°F.
Brush ribs on both sides with marinade. Arrange in a single layer in a large shallow baking dish. Cover and bake for 45 mins. Uncover and bake for 15 mins, or until ribs are browned.

title: smoked salmon and asparagus frittata
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Heat oil in a small skillet on medium-low heat. Cook onion, stirring occasionally, for 15 mins, until caramelized.
Meanwhile, cook potatoes in a saucepan of boiling water for 10 mins, until partially cooked. Drain.
Cook asparagus in a separate saucepan of boiling water for 1 min, until just tender. Use tongs to remove from pan. Drain, rinse under cold water and drain again.

Slice potatoes and arrange on bottom of a 6-cup baking dish. Top with layers of caramelized onion, smoked salmon, asparagus and feta. Lightly whisk eggs and milk. Season with pepper. Carefully pour into baking dish, taking care not to disturb layers.
Bake for 45 mins, until frittata is golden and just set. Serve with crusty bread.

title: creamy fish chowder
directions: Melt butter in a heavy-based saucepan on low heat. Saute onion for 5 minutes, until golden and soft.
Add potato and stir in flour. Add stock. Bring to a simmer. Cook for 10 minutes, until thick.
Add fish pieces and cook for 6 minutes, until tender. Stir in hot milk and heat slowly without boiling. Season to taste and stir in parsley.
Serve with a grinding of pepper and crusty bread.

title: gluten-free buttermilk muffins with walnut crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. For the crumble, mix 1 oz walnuts with 3 tbsp butter, 3 tbsp sugar, 3.5 oz gluten-free flour, and a pinch of salt, kneading into crumbs. Place in the fridge and chill for 30 minutes.

For the muffins, cream together 9 tbsp butter (1 stick + 1 tbsp), 2/3 cup sugar, vanilla extract and pinch of salt. Stir in the eggs one at a time, then fold in 7 oz gluten-free flour, baking powder and cocoa powder. Mix well then stir in the buttermilk. Drizzle the banana slices with lemon juice and fold into the batter with the remaining chopped nuts. Divide mixture between 12 muffin cups, top with the crumble and bake for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on a wire rack for about 1 hour.
Melt the chocolate in a bowl over a pan of warm water. Drizzle the chocolate over the muffins and allow to set for 30 minutes.

title: date and maple loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease an 8x5 inch loaf pan.
Combine dates and 1/3 cup boiling water in a small heatproof bowl. Stir in baking soda and let stand for 5 mins. Stir in maple syrup.

Meanwhile, in a stand mixer, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating until combined between additions. Add date mixture then stir in flour, in 2 batches. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 50 mins. Let cool in pan for 10 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Meanwhile, whisk ingredients for maple butter in a small bowl until combined. Serve loaf warm or cold with maple butter.

title: prosciutto and pine nut arancini
directions: Heat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Saute onion and garlic for 2-3 mins, until tender. Add prosciutto and pine nuts. Cook, stirring, for 2-3 mins. Increase heat to high and add rice. Stir for 1-2 mins, until rice is well coated. Add hot stock, 1 cup at a time, stirring continuously, for 20 mins, until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Add peas, parsley and Parmesan. Season. Spread risotto over a baking tray, cover and set aside to cool completely.

Line a separate baking tray with parchment paper. Shape risotto into 12 small balls, inserting a piece of mozzarella into the center of each. Roll in flour, dip in egg then coat in breadcrumbs. Place on prepared tray and chill for 15 mins.
Heat oil in a deep saucepan to 350°F. Deep-fry risotto balls, in batches, for 2-3 mins, until golden brown. Serve with lemon mayonnaise.
